            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <expan><abbr>D</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>anibus</ex></expan> <lb n="2"/>Vibius Emerit<lb break="no" n="3"/>us <expan><abbr>m</abbr><ex>iles</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>egionis</ex></expan> X <expan><abbr>g</abbr><ex>eminae</ex></expan> feci<supplied reason="lost">t pa</supplied><lb break="no" n="4"/><supplied reason="lost">rentibus suis Vib</supplied><lb break="no" n="5"/><supplied reason="lost">iae Vibi Ca</supplied><lb break="no" n="6"/><supplied reason="lost"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> et Vibio Maxi</supplied><lb break="no" n="7"/><supplied reason="lost">mino<certainty locus="name" match="preceding-sibling::text()" cert="low"/> patri <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>uo</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="8"/><supplied reason="lost">@(obito) <expan><abbr>anno</abbr><ex>rum</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="9"/><supplied reason="lost"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>V<certainty locus="name" match="preceding-sibling::text()" cert="low"/>DM<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></supplied> <lb n="0"/><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Kastengrabstein; oberhalb des Inschriftfeldes in der Mitte zwei weibliche Büsten und links und rechts je eine männliche Büste. Fundjahr: bereits um 1700 bekannt; 1885 an der angegebenen Fundstelle gesehen. Um 1890 waren das Ende der Z. 2 u. 3 und die rechten Hälften der Z. 4-9 noch erhalten: [---]VIS VIB / [---] VIBI CA / [---]O MAXI / [---]ATRI S / [---]NNO / [---]V(?)DM; damals erhaltene Höhe: (143) cm. Buchstabe E in Form von II geschrieben. Hedera in Z. 1.</p>
            </div>
